features: [Stylish and Sturdy] This storage ottoman features stylish linen-look fabric with fine stitching. Metal corner guards help reinforce the lid and thick MDF boards support the tops and sides, allowing the ottoman to hold a static load capacity of 660 lb
[Comfortable Seating] Filled with high-density foam and covered in linen-look fabric, this storage bench provides a soft, supportive, and breathable seat for optimal comfort

[Plenty of Storage Space] This folding ottoman, sized 15”D x 43"W x 15”H (38 x 110 x 38 cm) with a total capacity of 35 gallons, can be used to neatly organize your bed sheets, pillows, blankets, magazines, and more

[Easy to Set Up & Fold Away] With its unique folding design, this storage bench can be set up in just a few seconds. It conveniently folds flat for easy storage when not in use, saving space in your home

[Versatile Uses] Use this storage ottoman as a storage box, footstool, or even a coffee table! It can be placed anywhere you want, such as in the living room, at the end of your bed, in the foyer, or under a window

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks great and holds a lot
reviews.reviewText: This came in a flat box and was very easy to setup. It comes with dividers that I chose not to use. Just put them on the side of the ottoman. Don’t take up space and might use them later.I was very happy with the sleek design it has. Good fit for my living room or bedroom. The top is very strong and looks great. Like the tufts and buttons.Looks quality. I have 2 queen size comforters and six throws in mine. There is still some room. You can definitely sit on it. It is very sturdy. You can’t beat it for the price! I highly recommend this product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great and seems amazingly sturdy to sit on.
reviews.reviewText: This storage trunk/bench comes packed in a flat box and is easy to set up. It took a bit of maneuvering to get the lid to fit properly because it’s super snug (a good thing)—I had to place the back and sides of the lid onto the storage box first, then pull the front of the lid out a bit to fit onto the front of the storage trunk. It’s a tight fit. The trunk/bench is sturdy when sitting on it to put on shoes, and the fabric and tufted buttons seem to be well-made enough to hold up over time. I like it! It fits well at the bottom of a queen size Ikea Malm bed and mine is holding 3 sets of queen sheets with 6 queen pillow cases, 4 king size pillow cases, 2 quilt-style queen size comforters, 4 pillow quilt-style shams, 2 queen size pillows, 2 small lap blankets, plus some misc pillow protectors! A bit more narrow looking in width for the bottom of my Queen Ikea Malm bed than I’d like it to look, but for $50 it’s great. Larger storage benches are $150 and up typically (Target, etc). The dimensions on Amazon, the China packaging of the product, and the actual storage bench, are interestingly all different.Amazon ad:43 inches length x 15 in height x 15 in widthActual size:43 x 14 x 15.Box states:114.5 cm length (45 inches length)39.5 cm width (15 1/2 inches width)8.5 (3.35 inches height)I don’t use the divider that inserts into grooves down the middle of the trunk/Ben h to create 2 compartments —I slid it down the right side of the trunk/bench in case I need 2 compartments later and it fits there fine. The darker gray is neutral enough to coordinate with lots of furniture and bedding colors. Great purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is very compact and sits easily at the end of my bed and can easily be folded up and stored underneath your bed as well. If you want to switch it up I absolutely love this for all of my extra sheets and comforters. Definitely worth it. Also was very surprised that me and my son are able to sit on top of it while we’re watching TV as well. My son is around 40 pounds and I weigh 145 and it holds us with no problems.

reviews.reviewText: I bought one of these for use as extra storage, not as functional furniture, and it does not disappoint.Perfect size for my needs and has a decent amount of space, it is sturdy enough to sit on but I would not use it as a regular piece of furniture, I just got it but I can tell that it's not built with that in mind, IMHO.It is quite smelly, though.I opened it and left it open and in a bathroom with the window open overnight and still has that chemical smell, although it is smelling less today.Not a deal breaker for sure, as a matter of fact, I bought another one.

The fabric is soft and durable, and the color matches my sofa perfectly. The padded seat is comfortable and sturdy, and it can hold up to 660 lb. I use it as a footrest, a coffee table, and a storage box for my blankets and magazines. It is a versatile and practical piece of furniture that adds style and functionality to my home. I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a storage ottoman bench.
